    ISourceLocation, IASNode, IExpressionNode

    public final class NilNode
extends ExpressionNodeBase
    A nil node is a placeholder used to distinguish a missing optional node. Examples are "for (optE1; optE2; optE3)" or any positional construct of the form "x,,z"
